marked up, normally 2-3 times. some items like silk fans (largest size: 1'2") are posted as ¥60-75, but the lowest price is actually just ¥10. therefore it's often better to buy souvenirs somewhere just a few blocks away from the tourist spots. local chinese tourists have no issue with posted prices because they are all well trained in the art of bargaining. foreigners always pay more for everything negotiable in china but remember that chinese whose accents identify them as being from other provinces also pay higher prices than locals. the purchasing power of the nouveau riche in china makes 